title: Control 1
extract_protocol_ch1: Total circulatory RNA was extracted from from 200μL serum using the Plasma/Serum RNA Purification Mini Kit (Norgen Biotek Corporation, Thorold, Canada).
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Libraries were prepared using the Ion Total RNA-Seq Kit v2 protocol (Thermo Fisher, Revision E) using an equal RNA input of 5μL from every sample pooled into its respective library
description: total free circulating and exosomal RNA
data_processing: Torrent Suite v5.0.4 (Thermo Fisher) software used for basecalling.
data_processing.1: mirPRo software pipeline from Shi et al., Sci Rep, 2015. was used to perform quality control (QC), alignment and small RNA counting.
data_processing.2: Adapters were trimmed, clean, collapsed and count raw reads after which were mapped to the miRBase miRNA hairpin database (miRBase v21).
data_processing.3: Initial threshold filtering was performed on raw count data as follows: miRNA with two or fewer non-zero counts were selected as noise, with 10 counts selected as noise threshold. The miRNA read counts identified by the mirPRo pipeline were normalized for compositional bias in sequenced libraries and library size using the DESeq2 v1.15.28 package.
data_processing.4: Differential expression analysis was performed in R v3.3.2. Differential expression of miRNA read counts was performed using DESeq2. Pair-wise comparisons were generated between the different conditions of interest.
data_processing.5: Genome_build: miRBase miRNA hairpin database (miRBase v21)
data_processing.6: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab-delimited text file includes matrix of normalized abundance measurement for each library
